data = read_csv("mbti_1.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   type = col_character(),
##   posts = col_character()
## )
types <- data.frame(type =data$type )
sentences = str_split_fixed(data$posts,"\\|\\|\\|",50)
type_sen = cbind(types,sentences)
### get list that each element is for one type
type_name <- types %>% distinct() %>% unlist()
type_list <- vector("list", 16)
names(type_list) <- type_name 
for (i in 1:16){
  t<-  as.character(type_name[i])
  t_idx <- type_sen$type==t
  type_list[[t]]  <- c(as.matrix(type_sen[t_idx,-1]))
}

datatable(head(type_sen), style="bootstrap", class="table-condensed", options = list(dom = 'tp',scrollX = TRUE))

type_count <-as.data.frame(count(types,type)) %>% arrange(n)
ggplot() + geom_bar(data = type_count,aes(x=reorder(type,-n),y=n,fill=type),stat='identity')

count for each class 

diff_class <- str_split("IESNTFJP",'') %>% unlist()
type_mat <- matrix(nrow = dim(data)[1], ncol = 8)
colnames(type_mat) <- diff_class
for (i in 1:length(diff_class)){
  type_mat[,diff_class[i]] <- apply(types,1,function(x) return(ifelse(grepl(diff_class[i],x),1,0)))
}

diff_class_count <-apply(type_mat,2,sum)
diff_class_count <- data.frame(class = names(diff_class_count) , count = diff_class_count)
ggplot() + geom_bar(data = diff_class_count,aes(x=reorder(class,-count),y=count,fill=class),stat='identity')

tokenization We break the text into individual tokens which are simply individual words.

all_type_sen <- data.frame()
for (i in 1:16){
  temp <- data.frame(group=type_name[i],text = type_list[[type_name[i]]])
  all_type_sen <- rbind(all_type_sen,temp)
}

all_type_sen[,2] <- sapply(all_type_sen[,2], as.character)

all_type_sen %>% unnest_tokens(word,text) -> all_type_words

** 10 most commen words in all types ** i first filter stop words , numbers and punctto find real words in commen .

createBarPlotCommonWords = function(data,title)
{
  data %>% 
  filter(!word %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  count(word,sort = TRUE) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  mutate(word = factor(word, levels = rev(unique(word)))) %>%
  head(10) %>%
  
  ggplot(aes(x = word,y = n)) +
  geom_bar(stat='identity',colour="white") +
  geom_text(aes(x = word, y = 1, label = paste0("(",n,")",sep="")),
            hjust=0, vjust=.5, size = 4, colour = 'black',
            fontface = 'bold') +
  labs(x = 'Word', y = 'Word Count', 
       title = title) +
  coord_flip() + 
  theme_bw()

}

all_type_words <- all_type_words[!str_detect(all_type_words$word,"[:digit:]"),]
all_type_words <-  all_type_words[!str_detect(all_type_words$word,"[:punct:]"),]
createBarPlotCommonWords(all_type_words,'Top 10 most Common Words')

it can be seen that words such as people and time and love has more frequency . WordCloud of the Common Words

createWordCloud = function(data,tit)
{
  
  layout(matrix(c(1, 2), nrow=2), heights=c(2, 5))
  par(mar=rep(0, 4))
  plot.new()
  
  text(x=0.5, y=0.5, tit )
  data %>% 
  filter(!word %in% stop_words$word) %>%
  count(word,sort = TRUE) %>%
  ungroup()  %>%
  head(30) %>%
  with(wordcloud(word, n, max.words = 30,colors=brewer.pal(8, "Dark2")))
}

createWordCloud(all_type_words,'WordCloud of the Common Words')
